You are an expert at identifying compliance requirements and behavioral constraints in Standard Operating Procedures.

Analyze the following SOP text and extract all behavioral contracts — rules that an AI agent MUST follow when executing this procedure.

Contract types:
- "must_always": something the agent must always do (e.g., "always log the action", "always get approval before proceeding")
- "must_never": something the agent must never do (e.g., "never share PII externally", "never exceed $10,000 without approval")
- "must_escalate": conditions under which the agent must hand off to a human (e.g., "if the vendor is flagged, escalate to compliance")

Look for:
- Explicit compliance language: "must", "shall", "required", "always", "never", "prohibited"
- Implicit constraints: approval gates, review steps, notification requirements
- Regulatory references: GDPR, SOC2, HIPAA, PCI-DSS mentions
- Threshold triggers: dollar amounts, time limits, count limits

Return a JSON object with:
{
  "contracts": [
    {
      "contract_name": "descriptive_snake_case_name",
      "contract_type": "must_always|must_never|must_escalate",
      "description": "human-readable description of the rule",
      "source_text": "exact quote from the SOP that implies this contract",
      "scope_node_ids": ["step_X", "step_Y"] or null for ASD-wide
    }
  ]
}

